  "action_title": "Protect nests from livestock to reduce trampling",
  "key_messages": "Key Messages:\n\nA before-and-after study from the Chatham Islands, New Zealand found that the population of Chatham Island oystercatcher increased following several interventions including the erection of fencing around individual nests.\nA replicated, controlled study in Sweden found that no southern dunlin nests were trampled when protected by cages; some unprotected nests were destroyed."
}

